Description:
    Generates a Rails view and corresponding .vue file which gets mounted when the view is loaded.

Example:
    bin/rails generate view_with_vue show posts

    This will create:
        app/views/posts/show.html.erb
        app/frontend/entrypoints/views/posts/show/App.vue
        app/frontend/entrypoints/views/posts/show.ts
        "/posts/:id, to: 'posts#show' in config/routes.rb"
        a 'show' method in app/controllers/posts_controller.rb
